			    STPJS 318</div>
  <div class="topic">Excerpts from a Sermon by President Joseph Smith</div>
  <p class="right">July 23rd, 1843.</p>
  <p class="std">Last Monday morning certain men came to me and said: &ldquo;Brother Joseph, Hyrum is no
  prophet<span class="footRef">1</span>&mdash;he can&rsquo;t lead the church; you must lead the church. If you resign, all things will go wrong;
  you must not resign; if you do the church will be scattered.&rdquo;  I felt curious and said: &ldquo;Have we not
  learned the Priesthood after the order of Melchizedek,<span class="footRef">2</span> which includes both Prophets, Priests and
  Kings: see Rev. 1 Chap., 6th v.,<span class="footRef">3</span> and I will advance your Prophet to a Priest, and then to a King&mdash;not
  to the Kingdoms of this earth, but of the Most High God.<span class="footRef">4</span> See Rev. 5 Chap., 10th v.&mdash;&lsquo;Thou hast
  made us unto our God, Kings and Priests, and we shall reign on the earth.&rsquo;&rdquo;<span class="footRef">5</span></p>
  <p class="std">If I should be exalted would there not be a great many of my enemies disappointed in Missouri,
  when they wake up and find themselves in hell, see what they might have obtained,<span class="footRef">6</span> and realize what
  they have lost by not listening to my voice,<span class="footRef">7</span> and obeying my instructions?<span class="footRef">8</span></p>
  <p class="std">Matth. 5 Chap., 17 and 18 v.&mdash;&ldquo;Think not that I am come to destroy the law, or the prophets;
  I am not come to destroy but to fulfil. For verily I say unto you, till heaven and earth pass, one jot
  or one tittle shall in no wise pass from the law till all be fulfilled.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">9</span></p>
  <p class="std">And again, Matth. 11 Chap., 12 and 13 v.&mdash;&ldquo;And from the days of John the Baptist, until now,
  the Kingdom of Heaven suffereth violence, and the violent take it by force. For all the prophets and
  the law prophesied until John.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">10</span> John held the Aaronic Priesthood<span class="footRef">11</span> and was a legal administrator,
  and the forerunner of Christ, and came to prepare the way before him.<span class="footRef">12</span></p>
  <p class="std">Christ was the head of the Church,<span class="footRef">13</span> the chief corner stone,<span class="footRef">14</span> the spiritual rock<span class="footRef">15</span> upon which the
  church was built, and the gates of hell shall not prevail against it.<span class="footRef">16</span> He built up the Kingdom, chose
  Apostles,<span class="footRef">17</span> and ordained them to the Melchizedek Priesthood,<span class="footRef">18</span> giving them power to administer in
  the ordinances of the Gospel.<span class="footRef">19</span> John was a priest after the order of Aaron<span class="footRef">20</span> before Christ.</p>
  <p class="std">See Exodus 30 Chap. 30 and 31 v.&mdash;&ldquo;And thou shalt anoint Aaron and his sons, and consecrate
  them, that they may minister unto me in the priest&rsquo;s office. And thou shalt speak unto the children
  of Israel, saying, This shall be an holy anointing</p>
